description: Keith Haring, Salvador Dalí, David Hockney, Jean-Michel Basquiat, Roy Lichtenstein and others adorned the park's rides. Those attractions have been in shipping containers ever since — until now.
title: World famous artists designed this carnival in 1987. Nearly 40 years later, it's back

description: A bipartisan Senate bill, dropping Thursday, promises better health care for some of the poorest, sickest Americans, who are known as "duals" because they qualify for both Medicare and Medicaid.
title: Vulnerable Americans are stuck in a Medicare-Medicaid maze. Is a fix in sight?

description: SpaceX has successfully conducted a test launch of its massive Starship rocket in a major success for company, which saw the rocket explode in two previous test flights
title: Third time's the charm: SpaceX's massive Starship reaches space

description: An entire industry wouldn't exist without him, yet few know his name. In his songs, Knott challenged the faithful to examine their faults and hypocrisies.
title: Michael Knott, who changed the course of Christian rock, dies at 61

description: Dollar Tree plans to close about 600 Family Dollar stores in the first half of this year and 370 Family Dollar and 30 Dollar Tree stores over the next several years.
title: Dollar Tree to close nearly 1,000 stores as it posts a fourth quarter loss
